  "prompt": "Can you have sex, have a period, and still be pregnant?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to have sex while pregnant. Additionally, some women can experience light bleeding or spotting during pregnancy, which may be mistaken for a period. However, it's important to clarify that this bleeding is not a true menstrual period. Pregnancy involves the cessation of regular menstrual periods because the hormonal changes prevent the lining of the uterus from shedding.\n\nIf you suspect you are pregnant or are experiencing unusual bleeding, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional for an accurate diagnosis and appropriate guidance.",
